  "content": "ID: T1499.004\nTitle: Endpoint Denial of Service:Application or System Exploitation\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1499/004\nAdversaries may exploit software vulnerabilities that can cause an application or system to crash and deny availability to users. [1] Some systems may automatically restart critical applications and services when crashes occur, but they can likely be re-exploited to cause a persistent denial of service (DoS) condition. Adversaries may exploit known or zero-day vulnerabilities to crash applications and/or systems, which may also lead to dependent applications and/or systems to be in a DoS condition. Crashed or restarted applications or systems may also have other effects such as Data Destruction , Firmware Corruption , Service Stop etc. which may further cause a DoS condition and deny availability to critical information, applications and/or systems.",
  "category": "Article",
  "source": "Local Storage",
